ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Looking attractive to others is more important to me than being happy with who I am inside.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I try to imagine what my body looks like to others (i.e., like I am looking at myself from the outside).
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: How I look is more important to me than how I think or feel.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I choose specific clothing or accessories based on how they make my body appear to others.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: My physical appearance is more important than my personality.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: When I look in the mirror, I notice areas of my appearance that I think others will view critically.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I consider how my body will look to others in the clothing I am wearing.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I often think about how my body must look to others.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: My physical appearance says more about who I am than my intellect.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: How sexually attractive others find me says something about who I am as a person.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: My physical appearance is more important than my physical abilities.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I try to anticipate others' reactions to my physical appearance.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: My body is what gives me value to other people.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing

ElementDescription: I have thoughts about how my body looks to others even when I am alone.
Notes: 1= Strongly disagree; 2= Disagree; 3= Neither agree nor disagree; 4= Agree; 5= Strongly agree; 99= Missing
